The vice chairman of Myanmar opposition leader Aung San Suu Kyi's political party was threatened with arrest in a commentary in a government-run newspaper Sunday.
NLD Vice Chairman Tin Oo, 71, who has been imprisoned twice by Myanmar's military leaders, is a former defense minister, army commander in chief, Buddhist monk and lawyer.
Myanmar has barred British ministers and officials from the country following British pressure on the military regime to hold talks with opposition leader Aung San Suu Kyi.
Nearly 50 Burmese men, women and children demonstrated in the capital on Friday against military rule in their country.
